  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somalia: Supporting Justice Institutions to Reform the Penal Code and Criminal Procedure Code, and to Review and Adopt the Counterterrorism Bill</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To strengthen the Somali Penal Code. 2) To train, advise and mentor judicial actors on draft counter terrorism legislation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Somali Federal Ministry of Justice (MOJ); the National Parliamentary Sub-Committee on Justice and Regional Administrations; the Judiciary; the Somali Bar Association; women&#x2019;s groups; civil society organizations; Interim Regional Administrations; the Parliamentary Justice Committee; the Human Rights Parliamentary Committee; and the Somali public.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of trials for accused terrorists and organized criminals in Somalia, in accordance with the Provisional Constitution and international human rights law, and to enhance capacity of the Judiciary to combat terrorism offenses in Somalia.</narrative>
  </description>
